<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/792: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-24T17:00:00-05:00">August 24, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 25—1:48 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>38. At personal request of Mrs. Ayora President and family are my guests
                            in this Legation. Granting of temporary sanctuary is in my opinion fully
                            justified until danger to personal safety of President has passed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>